Package fr.inria.lille.shexjava.validation

Class RefineValidation

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.inria.lille.shexjava.validation.ValidationAlgorithm
      • fr.inria.lille.shexjava.validation.SORBEBasedValidation
        • fr.inria.lille.shexjava.validation.RefineValidation
  • public class RefineValidation
extends SORBEBasedValidation
    Implements the Refinement validation algorithm. Refine validation systematically constructs a complete typing for all nodes in the graph and for a set of selected shape in the schema. See in typing for the selected shape. It is therefore suited for cases when a complete typing is needed. The typing is computed at the first call of validate.
    Author:
    Jérémie Dusart, Iovka Boneva, Antonin Durey

      • validate

        public boolean validate​(org.apache.commons.rdf.api.RDFTerm focusNode,
                        Label label)
                 throws Exception
        Description copied from class: ValidationAlgorithm
        Constructs a shape map that allows to validate a focus node against a type. return true is focusNode has shape label, false otherwise. The constructed shape map can be retrieved using ValidationAlgorithm.getTyping()
        Specified by:
        validate in class ValidationAlgorithm
        Parameters:
        focusNode - The focus node for which the shape map is to be complete. If null, then the shape map will be complete for all nodes. The node might not belong to the graph, in which case it does not have a neighborhood.
        label - The label for which the shape map is to be complete. If null, then the shape map will be complete for all labels.
        Throws:
        Exception
